2500|$|Madoff {{founded the}} Wall Street firm Bernard L. Madoff <b>Investment</b> <b>Securities</b> LLC in 1960, and was its {{chairman}} until his arrest on December 11, 2008. The firm {{was one of}} the top market maker businesses on Wall Street, which bypassed [...] "specialist" [...] firms by directly executing orders over the counter from retail brokers. At the firm, he employed his brother Peter as senior managing director and chief compliance officer, Peter's daughter Shana Madoff, as the firm's rules and compliance officer and attorney, and his sons Andrew and Mark. Peter has since been sentenced to 10 years in prison and Mark committed suicide by hanging exactly two years after his father's arrest. Andrew died of lymphoma on September 3, 2014.|$|E
